	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think it's worth the effort to work on 1HS.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reason is that you can buy 1HS weapons cheaper then you can get comporable piercing weapons.  It doesn't matter in combat if your 12/24 offhander is piercing or slashing.  But, it does matter in price.<br><br>Besides, there are some very nice 1HS weapons with great stats.  Take, for example, the Centi Longsword which you can probably buy for around 2000pp or a little less.  It's 1HS, 14/27 with +8STR and +8STA.  What do you think it would sell for if it were a piercing weapon?  Probably about 5k or more.  Because rogues need piercers for Backstabbing, all piercing weapons are automatically worth more.<br><br>Sorry for the rambling response.  In a nutshell, yes, work on 1HS.<br>&nbsp;<br>Fluxus<br>Officer of Forbidden Legion<br>Tarew Marr<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160</a></td></tr>
