	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey, Ghetty.&nbsp;&nbsp;Check out my Magelo profile (in my sig).  You can probably get all of that stuff for 15K.  Maybe get a better BP... like Barbed Ringmail.  Might want some 6/65 rings instead of the +6STR/+6DEX rings I'm wearing too.  Also, since the mrylokar gear won't work for you until 46th lvl, I wouldn't waste time getting that stuff.<br><br>Other than Mrylo, I'd suggest a BA Coif on your head (AC8, +6STR, +6 all resists).  Shimmering Terrorhide boots are nice for your feet.  Dwarven Work Boots are OK too.  Mithril Arms are OK, but the AC is kinda low.  Get a hero bracer if your race can wear (halflings can't).<br><br>I'd also say spend a healthy chunk of your money on good weapons.  Pick up a nice 12 or 13 damage piercer for primary to bump up your backstab damage (small dragonbone shard is great), and something decent and fast in your offhand (shaded dagger or crystaline spider fang should work nicely).<br>&nbsp;<br>Fluxus<br>Officer of Forbidden Legion<br>Tarew Marr<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160</a></td></tr>
