<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102725887250020></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102725887250020><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102725887250020>RE: Rage Bringer</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102725887250020#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=121232><span id= >Fluxus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>126 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Jul 21st 9:53 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's my experience...<br><br>Founy:&nbsp;&nbsp;Picked him dry for three consecutive spawns.  He aggroed after about the 25th or so PP attempt.  I easily made it to the zone line each time.  The 4th Founy spawn yielded the note after the 3rd pick.<br><br>Tani:  I am KOS in Neriak even with DE Illusion.  H/S to the rogue guild.  Had a low-level DE go up to Tani and target him while I was up on top of the building.  Then, I assisted the DE so that I would target Tani.  I turned off attack (from assisting) and started to PP.  You become visible once you /assist but you won't get aggro from that spot.  I got the note on the 6th PP.  <br><br>That technique against Tani is often referred to as the z-axis exploit.  You're basically picking his pockets while 6 feet above his head and separated by the roof of a building.  It's like climbing up on top of your house and magically reaching down and stealing the TV while others are watching it without them noticing it.  It's an exploit.  You'll have to decide for yourself if you think it's 'honorable' to acquire the note this way or not.  <br><br>One other thing... the note is NOT No Drop, so you could pay another rogue to get it for you.  I'm not recommending any course of action, but just pointing out your options.<br><br>I just finished the Stanos and Eldreth turn-ins.  I'm going to Hate today, and also have another Hate trip planned for Monday in case the Book is not there today.<br>&nbsp;<br>Fluxus<br>Officer of Forbidden Legion<br>Tarew Marr<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160</a></td></tr>
