<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102624154582932></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102624154582932><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102624154582932>RE: Race and PVP for Rouges</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102624154582932#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>327 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 9th 3:16 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.34]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The answer to that is - it depends.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are going to PvP you will need poisons.  That is not cheap.  But it makes your likelyhood of survival and victory increase a great deal. Rogues are not stand up tank/melee types. If you are going to PvP you need to remember that stealth and timing are critical.  You need to pick the time and the place for the fight.  The place should be one that gives you the best advantage. The time should be when the target is not paying attention and is at his/her weakest. You are a rogue.  You do not have the HP or AC for an honorable fight like other melee classes.  Anyway, what do rogues care about honor?<br><br>Choose targets carefully. Go in slowly, undetected and strike from behind with everything you have. Remember that its best if you initiate the combat.  If you are attacked first I suggest running if you can.<br><br>Everyone in PvP is so hyped on Magic, Fire, and Cold resist that poison and disease resists go lacking. Stock up on pumice stones and make sure your MR is high.  Use blind poisons - my personal favorite - for opening attacks.  Don't forget to use your Disarm skill liberally. <br><br>Weapons with very low delay are best against casters.  Fastest caster spells without Focus Items have an equivelent weapon delay of about 20 (2 sec cast time).  If your weapon delay is faster than that you increase the probability of interrupting the caster.<br><br>Don't count on weapons with procs. They are nice when they do happen but they are unreliable.<br><br>For tanks follow up blind poisons with DD and DOT and Paralying Root poisons (nice root+slow). For casters you can use DD and DOT effectively since they don't have a lot of HP to begin with. Mana drains are nice, too, but I think DD poisons end the fight faster.  <br><br>Don't PvP bards.  Best you can usually hope for against a skilled bard is a draw.  <br><br>Your worst enemy - the See Invisibility spell.<br><br>If PvPing other rogues remember - &quot;what's good for the goose is good for the gander.&quot;  That rogue will do all of the above to you. And Pumice stones don't remove poison counters.<br><br>I think that hits some key points. Anyone else have any suggestions?<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

