	   <tr><td colspan=2>Interesting discussion here.&nbsp;&nbsp;Personally, if Xamurai wants to Twink his rogue, I say more power to him.  There's a lot of great gear out there for halfling rogues and with a lot of plat, you can make him quite powerful.<br><br>The only real danger here is that because your twinkie will be so much more powerful than the mobs you'll be fighting is that you'll misplay your rogue.  I only say that because it sounds like you're going to take the Power-Level route in addition to twinking.  Maybe not...<br><br>But, if you PL your rogue with a druid or cleric or whatever, you will neglect skills like backstab.  You will also not understand how to properly play your rogue in a group environment. Playing a rogue is different than any other class.  Unlike a tank, you want to stay behind a mob and understand how to control aggro (aggro=bad).  You'll need to know when to engage a mob.  You'll need to understand the fine art of Evading in battle, as well as your role as a CR specialist.  You'll need to work on Pick Lock and Pick Pocket.  If you straight-out PL your rogue, letting him tank red mobs while another toon sits to the side throwing out heals, you're Backstab skill will suffer.<br><br>I think leveling a non-twink, non-PL'd rogue is honorable.  That's the route I took.  But, there's nothing wrong with equipping your rogue with nice gear.  It sounds like you know people will consider you a Twink and you don't really care.  Just so long as you also understand that if you PL your twink, you may end up at 60th lvl losing groups and dying a lot because you never took the time to properly learn how to play your rogue.<br><br>Good luck to you.<br><br>(and if you're on Tarew Marr, can you buy me a couple of blood points and a new BP?  :P  )<br>&nbsp;<br>Fluxus<br>Officer of Forbidden Legion<br>Tarew Marr<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=138160</a></td></tr>
