	   <tr><td colspan=2>Not that I am dead set oppsoed to twinking but since rogues are very much and equipment based character, twinking takes all the fun out of it.&nbsp;&nbsp;Anyway most of the best rogue armor is no drop anyhow.<br><br>I suggest starting your low level rogue off simple, if you feel you must twink at all: banded armor or blackend alloy (looks cooler). Netherbian Unguis and shiny brass shield until you get dual wield.  Then get blackend alloy longsword for you off hand.  Grow into your equipment.<br><br>In your high teens try a Stilleto of the Bloodclaw for a weapon.  Eventually get a Serrated Bone dirk and a Sturdy Grimling Mining Pick ( I still use the pick and I am 41).<br><br>Since rogues are heavily skill based forget PL'ing.  You need the skills to advance with your level in a timely fashion.  <br><br>A rogue is a thinking persons character.  A hack and slash rogue is a dead rogue.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
