	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey I never said I was a rogue &quot;expert&quot; I don't know what you consider yourself but I don't ask many people for advice other than close friends, on top of it I had to work the same amount for my monk (my main) and my necro (which I leveled basically about the same time) they're both wearing magnificent stuff now and the reason I moreso NEED my rogue to lvl quickly (and also wanted becuase I think rogues are cool) is because I am coming into a new &quot;uber&quot; (so to speak) guild and the requirements for entering are to have so much met.&nbsp;&nbsp;I have acquired 49 AA points on my necro and almost twice as many on my monk (this is addressed to the guy who said if I'm bored with EQ go to another game).  I enjoy EQ a lot and I understand how much you learn from doing things the hard way but way I figure is I've learned enough about the game to twink (I mean I know the stuff that you learn with your first character IE the tactics needed to survive).  I don't see anyhthing wrong.  I mean I'm learning to play my rogue just like anyone else would only with more rapidity so to speak.  I also try to stick to lower exp. mobs to raise skills. I am now lvl 12 and have my 1hs 2hs and pierce maxed for my lvl as well I've been working on other skills such as sense heading, alcohol tolerance, and fishing.  So if you think I twinked SOLELY to reach 60 ASAP then no. I have a friend who made a rogue to lvl 60 in 8 days playing time using 3 accounts (all are his).  Using his 60 cleric and 57 druid he now has a lvl 60 rogue to boast.  I only use 1 account, I don't believe in &quot;wasting&quot; money to power level myself and I understand why some despise twinking.  I mean I hated seeing twinks when I first started my monk.  I was jealous and at the same time disgusted by it.  However once I reached levels sufficient to go gain better stuff I reached the ranks with the others.  I think my twinking is somehow &quot;owed&quot; to me for all the bull@#%^ I had to put up with (I.E. dealing with hell levelz ect. in oldschool) hey I worked for the money I even worked for some of the equipment.  So to those who still think me &quot;bad&quot; for it.  Well I'm sorry but I think I worked just as hard as anyone else to get my stuff, only thing is I had an easier time because I had 2 lvl 50+ which I might add I WORKED FOR MYSELF (I even soloed my necro about 50 lvlz of his 57) so if you still think me unworthy and/or undeserving well I don't know what to say except... Another rogue has joined the ranks.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
