<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102533374227265></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102533374227265><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102533374227265>RE: smithing</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=2&mid=102533374227265#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=166256><span id= >Restyn</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>52 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jun 29th 3:05 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>13? And looking to do smithing? Hmm, well, I would say GFay. You can run up to Crushbone and slaughter orcs (and still get xp from legionnaires and the CB belts) plus, the orcs drop rusty weapons. Take the weapons and sharpen them (to tarnished) then convert them to bricks of ore. This will get you to smithing in the 20s. Then take the ore, break it into pieces, make the pieces into studs .... smithing of 30s, without buying any ore! Keep going with lanterns and toolboxes and you should be able to get into the 50s.<br><br>Check out www.eqtraders.com for exact info on trade skills though.<br>&nbsp;<br>Restyn<br>Rogue of Saryrn Server<br>32 Seasons</td></tr>
